<title>GHANA: Ghana raises cocoa producer price 50 pct.</title>
<headline>Ghana raises cocoa producer price 50 pct.</headline>
<dateline>ACCRA 1997-06-12</dateline>
<text>
<p>Ghana raised official cocoa prices paid to producers by 50 percent on Thursday, to 1.8 million cedis a tonne from 1.2 million cedis, Deputy Finance Minister Victor Selormey said on Thursday.</p>
<p>The rise would have immediate effect and represented 54 percent of the estimated Free-On-Board (FOB) price for the mid-crop season which opens next month, he said at a meeting of Ghana's Cocoa Board (COCOBOD) and Producer Price Review Committee officials, farmers, buyers and hauliers.</p>
<p>He said the new price represents the government's commitment to &quot;increase progressively the producer price until it reaches at least 60 percent of the FOB price by the year 2,000.&quot;</p>
<p>-- Matthew Bunce, Abidjan newsroom + 225 21 90 90</p>
